      },
      "date": "2013-05-06 16:22:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThis looks like a step in the right direction to me.  Although I'd argue you could go a little farther and convert many of those CERRORs to CDEBUGs.  In my opinion if a message isn't going to be useful to a Lustre admin (not a Lustre developer) then it probably should not go to the console.",
